HEADWORD: blood berry
<hw>blood" ber*ry</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A bushy houseplant (<spn>Rivina humilis</spn>) having white to pale
pink flowers followed by racemes of scarlet berries; it is native to the
tropical Americas.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> rougeberry, rouge plant.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

